article.headline: Oral Roberts 89, UMKC 54
article.story: TULSA, Okla. -- Dominique Morrison scored 18 points and a couple of runs in the second half helped Oral Roberts cruise to an 89-54 victory over Missouri-Kansas City Thursday night. Morrison made 6-of-9 shots from the field, including one trey, and was 5-of-6 on free throws for the Golden Eagles (9-11, 7-1 Summit League), who have won six games in a row. Marcus Lewis and Andre Hardy added 14 points each for Oral Roberts. The Golden Eagles led 41-28 at intermission and the Kangaroos, led by Bakari Lewis' 13 points, never got any closer. After the teams traded baskets to open the second half, Oral Roberts went on a 12-3 surge to increase its lead to 55-33. UMKC (6-15, 2-6) cut its deficit to 66-50 with six minutes left, but the Golden Eagles scored nine straight points. Oral Roberts ended the game on a 14-2 run.
